// Shared "runtime bag" for the useVoice hook split.
//
// useVoice is a ref-and-callback heavy infrastructure hook.  Most of its body
// used to be thin wrapper functions that bundle a few stable refs/setters and
// forward to a corresponding `*Runtime` helper under voice/.  To slim the hook
// down, those wrappers are now generated by factories (see voiceBindings,
// voiceConversationStarters, voiceLifecycleControls, voiceTestEntries).  Each
// factory takes a single VoiceRuntimeBag and returns a group of bound
// functions.
//
// The bag also carries mutable "holders" (lifecycleHolder / enginesHolder /
// bindingsHolder).  These solve the late-binding problem: bindings need to be
// able to reference lifecycle.startVoiceConversation (e.g. via the bus
// effects) even though lifecycle is built _after_ bindings.  Holders let
// callers grab the slot lazily — by the time anything actually fires, all
// slots are populated.

